{"type":"message","id":"b265485b","parentId":"f87f5a0b","timestamp":"2026-06-16T16:00:46.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"cab7babfec5143c79a27a0001e24d146","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"searchQueries\": [\n    \"AI tools for full-stack developers TypeScript JavaScript 2026 latest news\"\n  ],\n  \"provider\": \"parallel-free\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 3728,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"parallel-free\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fab34c3c72d2aba5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe 10 Best AI Coding Tools in 2026  -  Developers Digest\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fab34c3c72d2aba5\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.developersdigest.tech/blog/best-ai-coding-tools-2026\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"86212fad642f3ae2\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nDevelopers Digest\\n\\nDevelopers Digest\\n\\nDEVDIGEST\\n\\nVideos and open-source projects at the intersection of AI and development\\n\\nWeekly AI dev insights. Free.\\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\nPrivacy Policy · Terms of Service · Contact\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"86212fad642f3ae2\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.developersdigest.tech\",\n      \"published\": \"2026-06-02\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"86212fad642f3ae2\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nDevelopers Digest\\n\\nDevelopers Digest\\n\\nDEVDIGEST\\n\\nVideos and open-source projects at the intersection of AI and development\\n\\nWeekly AI dev insights. Free.\\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\nPrivacy Policy · Terms of Service · Contact\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"86212fad642f3ae2\\\">>>\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"605f6aec1c27bd01\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTop 12 AI Developer Tools in 2026: Coding Assistants, Agents & Security Tools\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"605f6aec1c27bd01\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://checkmarx.com/learn/ai-security/top-12-ai-developer-tools-in-2026-for-security-coding-and-quality\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"55eafb4a190856fe\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI developer tools are software products and services that use artificial intelligence to automate, enhance, or streamline aspects of software development. These tools integrate AI technologies such as machine learning, natural language processing, and deep learning into developers’ workflows. Their core aim is to reduce repetitive tasks, improve code quality, accelerate delivery cycles, and enable smarter development environments.\\n\\nBy automating processes like code generation, security scanning, testing, documentation, and debugging, AI developer tools are shifting traditional roles in software engineering. Rather than just assisting with isolated pieces like syntax correction or suggestions, modern tools increasingly provide support across the development lifecycle. As a result, teams that adopt these tools typically see a reduction in manual effort and improved consistency, reliability, and maintainability of their codebases.\\nThis is part of a series of articles about [AI cybersecurity](https://checkmarx.com/learn/ai-security/ai-cybersecurity-6-solutions-transforming-appsec-and-the-soc/) .\\n\\n## Methodology – How we Selected These Dev Tools\\n\\nWe selected tools that are widely adopted or rapidly emerging in 2025–2026, then evaluated them against practical enterprise criteria: (1) Developer workflow fit (IDE/PR/CI/CD), (2) Quality and reliability of outputs (3) Security guardrails for AI-generated code, (4) Data privacy and governance controls, and (5) ability to scale across teams (developers, AppSec, DevOps, leadership).\\n\\nWhere available, we also included user-reported limitations to highlight real-world tradeoffs.\\n\\n## AI Developer Tools at a Glance\\n\\nLet’s cut to the chase. Here are the top AI developer tools, organized according to the most common enterprise use cases. Click on the names of the solutions, or scroll down, for a detailed tool-by-tool analysis.\\n|**Category** |**Tool** |**Strengths** |**Things to Consider** |\\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\\n|Agentic AI Security Tools |[Checkmarx One Assist](https://checkmarx.com/product/checkmarx-one-assist/) |Multi-layer agentic AppSec across IDE, CI/CD, and portfolio governance – reduces noise, apply policy context, and accelerate secure remediation for AI-speed development. |Highest value comes with workflow rollout (IDE + CI/CD + governance) and clear guardrails (scope, policies, approvals) so actions remain controlled and auditable. |\\n|Code Assistants and Vibe Coding |GitHub Copilot |Deep IDE integration, autonomous coding, natural language support |Suggestions require manual review; subscription costs |\\n|Code Assistants and Vibe Coding |Tabnine |Strong privacy, LLM flexibility, customizable team policies |Lower suggestion quality in some cases; compatibility varies |\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"55eafb4a190856fe\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"checkmarx.com\",\n      \"published\": \"2026-03-24\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"55eafb4a190856fe\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI developer tools are software products and services that use artificial intelligence to automate, enhance, or streamline aspects of software development. These tools integrate AI technologies such as machine learning, natural language processing, and deep learning into developers’ workflows. Their core aim is to reduce repetitive tasks, improve code quality, accelerate delivery cycles, and enable smarter development environments.\\n\\nBy automating processes like code generation, security scanning, testing, documentation, and debugging, AI developer tools are shifting traditional roles in software engineering. Rather than just assisting with isolated pieces like syntax correction or suggestions, modern tools increasingly provide support across the development lifecycle. As a result, teams that adopt these tools typically see a reduction in manual effort and improved consistency, reliability, and maintainability of their codebases.\\nThis is part of a series of articles about [AI cybersecurity](https://checkmarx.com/learn/ai-security/ai-cybersecurity-6-solutions-transforming-appsec-and-the-soc/) .\\n\\n## Methodology – How we Selected These Dev Tools\\n\\nWe selected tools that are widely adopted or rapidly emerging in 2025–2026, then evaluated them against practical enterprise criteria: (1) Developer workflow fit (IDE/PR/CI/CD), (2) Quality and reliability of outputs (3) Security guardrails for AI-generated code, (4) Data privacy and governance controls, and (5) ability to scale across teams (developers, AppSec, DevOps, leadership).\\n\\nWhere available, we also included user-reported limitations to highlight real-world tradeoffs.\\n\\n## AI Developer Tools at a Glance\\n\\nLet’s cut to the chase. Here are the top AI developer tools, organized according to the most common enterprise use cases. Click on the names of the solutions, or scroll down, for a detailed tool-by-tool analysis.\\n|**Category** |**Tool** |**Strengths** |**Things to Consider** |\\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\\n|Agentic AI Security Tools |[Checkmarx One Assist](https://checkmarx.com/product/checkmarx-one-assist/) |Multi-layer agentic AppSec across IDE, CI/CD, and portfolio governance – reduces noise, apply policy context, and accelerate secure remediation for AI-speed development. |Highest value comes with workflow rollout (IDE + CI/CD + governance) and clear guardrails (scope, policies, approvals) so actions remain controlled and auditable. |\\n|Code Assistants and Vibe Coding |GitHub Copilot |Deep IDE integration, autonomous coding, natural language support |Suggestions require manual review; subscription costs |\\n|Code Assistants and Vibe Coding |Tabnine |Strong privacy, LLM flexibility, customizable team policies |Lower suggestion quality in some cases; compatibility varies |\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"55eafb4a190856fe\\\">>>\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"565c874c5d179ee9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n7 AI tools every developer must know in 2026 - YouTube\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"565c874c5d179ee9\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1AMimclTvFw\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"011542e5dc5ae881\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n7 AI tools every developer must know in 2026\\n\\n[Sanket Singh](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCuDfiQK9CGFc4Tiz6MrdZ_A)\\n\\nSubscribe\\n\\nSubscribed\\n\\n👋 Hello Humans, I’m Sanket Singh, currently working as a Software Engineer.\\nPreviously, I’ve worked at Google, Microsoft, LinkedIn, and InterviewBit. I am also a former Google Summer of Code Student Developer under the Berkman Klein Center at Harvard University.\\nMy expertise lies in Tech, Engineering, Software Development, and Coding. Here, I’ll be sharing insights, resources, and updates around these topics to help you grow in your tech journey.\\nDISCLAIMER: All opinions shared on this channel are our own and don't express views or opinions of our employers. We only use our experiences and public knowledge to make our content. NO CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION of our employers is used or shared on this channel. This is not a Professional Coaching channel, it only highlights the public resources that have worked for our careers.\\n📩 For business and collaboration enquiries: singhsanket110398@gmail.com\\n\\n[Coding Is Becoming Tokenmaxxing in 2026 12:23](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JgP1LWjA17U)\\n\\n[AI has changed System Design Roadm